               <floruit notBefore="0284" notAfter="0316">St Sisinnius was one of the so-called equestrian saints, 
                  died as a martyr in <placeName ref="LOC1481Antioc">Antioch</placeName>
                  during the persecution of <persName ref="PRS3581Diocleti">Diocletian</persName> from <date>284 </date> to <date>316</date>. 
                  His martyrdom is commemorated on 26 Barmūdah in the Coptic calendar = <date type="diesNatalis" ref="ethiocal:Miyazya26">26 Miyāzyā</date>.
                  In the Ethiopic narrative (following the Coptic) the 4th-century martyr is conflanted with the legendary (first to second century CE) figure of the Byzantine folklore of the same name, who combatted a female demon (<persName ref="PRS10134Werzely">Wǝrzǝlyā</persName>)
                  St Sisinnius is frequently depicted on the walls of churches and in manuscripts alongside other holy riders. </floruit>
